ğŸ“Œ Java: Why void methods cannot be printed
ğŸ” Problem Example
class square {
    int side;
    Scanner in = new Scanner(System.in);

    public void getValues() {   // ğŸ‘ˆ void method
        System.out.println("Enter side of Square");
        side = in.nextInt();
    }

    public int area() {
        return side * side;
    }
}

public class Q3 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        square cla = new square();
        System.out.println(cla.getValues());   // âŒ ERROR
        System.out.println(cla.area());        // âœ… works
    }
}

âš ï¸ Why error occurs?

void = method does not return anything.

But System.out.println(cla.getValues()); tries to print a return value.

Since nothing is returned â†’ compiler error.

âœ… Correct Usage
public class Q3 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        square cla = new square();
        cla.getValues();                     // âœ… just call void method
        System.out.println(cla.area());      // âœ… prints result
    }
}

ğŸ“– Notes

Void methods

Perform an action (input, update, print, etc.).

Do not return any value.

Call them simply:

obj.methodName();


Non-void methods

Return a value (e.g., int, String, double).

Can be printed or stored:

System.out.println(obj.methodName());
int result = obj.methodName();


âœ… Key Rule to Remember:
ğŸ‘‰ void = â€œdo somethingâ€
ğŸ‘‰ non-void = â€œgive me somethingâ€